Preheat the oven to 400 degrees. Halve the @zucchini{32%ounce} lengthwise, then scoop
out the seedy area with a #spoon{}. Place on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} and
toss with a large drizzle of @olive oil{} and a large pinch of @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Place in the oven, cut side down, and roast for ~{20-25%minutes},
until soft and golden brown on the bottom.

While the squash roasts, bring @water{2%cups} and the @veggie stock concentrate{2} to
a boil in a #small pot{}. Add the @quinoa{1%cup}, cover, and simmer for
~{15%minutes}, until tender.

Meanwhile, finely chop the @button mushrooms{8%ounce}(chopped). Halve, peel, and
mince the @shallot{4%ounce}(minced). Mince or grate the @garlic{4%clove}(minced).
Halve, seed, and finely dice the @Roma tomato{4}(diced). Strip the
@thyme{1/2%ounce}(chopped) off the sprigs and finely chop the leaves.
Finely chop the @parsley{1/4%ounce}(chopped).

Heat @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the shallots
and cook, tossing, for ~{2-3%minutes}, until soft. Add a large drizzle of
@olive oil{3%teaspoon}, the mushrooms, tomatoes, and thyme to the pan.
Cook for another ~{5-6%minutes}, until very soft and cooked down. Add the garlic
and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until fragrant. Season with salt and pepper.

Add the @Parmesan cheese{2%ounce} and @quinoa{3/4%cup}(cooked) to the pan and
toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.

Once ready, remove the zucchinis from the oven and stuff with as much quinoa
mixture as will fit. Heat the broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees. Sprinkle
the zucchini boats with Parmesan cheese and return to the oven until the cheese
is golden brown and melted.

Plate the remaining quinoa mixture. Serve the zucchini boats on top of the
remaining quinoa and sprinkle with parsley. Enjoy!

> Zucchini is the perfect vessel for stuffing—once scooped out, their seedy
> centers form a tiny boat for filling. Finely chopped mushrooms are
> sautéed with butter and shallot for a riff on mushroom duxelles, a classic
> French preparation. Folded into a quinoa stuffing, it's divine!